{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Adrian Beria Blog","author":"Adrian Beria"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"dd12398b-d7e5-5ad7-84ce-042bd61b8006","excerpt":"Introduction Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used…","html":"<h2>Introduction</h2>\n<p>Redux Thunk middleware allows you to write action creators that return a function instead of an action. The thunk can be used to delay the dispatch of an action, or to dispatch only if a certain condition is met. The inner function receives the store methods dispatch and getState as parameters.</p>\n<h2>What is a middleware</h2>\n<p>The middleware sits in between the dispatch and reducers, which means we can alter our dispatched actions before they get to the reducers or execute some code during the dispatch.</p>\n<h2>When to use</h2>\n<p>When we need to do any kind of asynchronous logic, we generally pair it with axios, which is a library for making HTTP requests. One of my favorite reasons to use axios over ES6 fetch is that with axios you don’t have to do convert the data you obtained from your request usding .json(), axios does this automatically, for example:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">fetch(url).then(response =&gt; response.json()).then(data =&gt; console.log(data))\n\naxios.get(url).then(response =&gt; console.log(response))</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Installing dependencies</h2>\n<p>For an alredy created project:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add redux react-redux</code></pre></div>\n<p>If you’re doing some async</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">yarn add axios redux-thunk</code></pre></div>\n<h2>Project structure</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>src</p>\n<ul>\n<li>actions</li>\n<li>api</li>\n<li>components</li>\n<li>pages</li>\n<li>reducers</li>\n<li>store</li>\n<li>types</li>\n<li>App.js</li>\n<li>index.js</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Each folder will have an index.js file inside.</p>\n<h2>Types</h2>\n<p>Inside the types folder we add our constants</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 544px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 21.507352941176467%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/c2e61/redux-thunk-1.png 148w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/08c14/redux-thunk-1.png 295w,\n/static/4092180e8335a6d19ddd15b9703a1530/ff67a/redux-thunk-1.png 544w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 544px) 100vw, 544px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>Actions</h2>\n<p>Inside the actions folder we add our actions creator, importing the constants we made.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/redux-thunk-2.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 20.802919708029197%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/redux-thunk-2.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/1a291/redux-thunk-2.png 148w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/2bc4a/redux-thunk-2.png 295w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/fb8a0/redux-thunk-2.png 590w,\n/static/6e924fbc690e64eaad420bedc09a85a5/3edcd/redux-thunk-2.png 822w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>API</h2>\n<p>This is where we will use axios, we will do all our requests on these folders and it will look like this.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/139d2/redux-thunk-3.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 13.6226034308779%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/fb8a0/redux-thunk-3.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/1a291/redux-thunk-3.png 148w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/2bc4a/redux-thunk-3.png 295w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/fb8a0/redux-thunk-3.png 590w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/526de/redux-thunk-3.png 885w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/fa2eb/redux-thunk-3.png 1180w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/08f6a/redux-thunk-3.png 1770w,\n/static/802f5a5003bfcdf441ee670609aef96b/139d2/redux-thunk-3.png 1982w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>The URL we’re using is a server we created using JSON Server which gives us a service with information we can do CRUD operations to, when we build the next project we will see this in more detail.</p>\n<h2>Reducer</h2>\n<p>This is where our reducer will be, anytime we dispatch an action in our app, the reducer recieves the command to change the global state</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/98366/redux-thunk-4.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 138.04780876494024%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/fb8a0/redux-thunk-4.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/1a291/redux-thunk-4.png 148w,\n/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/2bc4a/redux-thunk-4.png 295w,\n/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/fb8a0/redux-thunk-4.png 590w,\n/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/526de/redux-thunk-4.png 885w,\n/static/ec80b1067e0447ce5cd99b678006c9b0/98366/redux-thunk-4.png 1004w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Notice how it only does something when we do only a fetch request, its because our POST, DELETE and PUT will only do a HTTP request and won’t mess with the global state, but when we do a GET the app will reload.</p>\n<h2>Store</h2>\n<p>This is where our store will be configured.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/c5669/redux-thunk-5.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 24.834437086092716%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/fb8a0/redux-thunk-5.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/1a291/redux-thunk-5.png 148w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/2bc4a/redux-thunk-5.png 295w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/fb8a0/redux-thunk-5.png 590w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/526de/redux-thunk-5.png 885w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/fa2eb/redux-thunk-5.png 1180w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/08f6a/redux-thunk-5.png 1770w,\n/static/c2604077dc021a529dfdbadda762b1a7/c5669/redux-thunk-5.png 1812w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<p>Not much to see, we create the store taking as arguments the rootReducer, the initial state and with composeEnhancers we can add several middlewares like Redux Thunk.</p>\n<h2>Connect Store to Provide</h2>\n<p>We configure our store importing the setup from store folder.</p>\n<p>\n  <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/08cdb/redux-thunk-6.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n  \n  <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n    style=\"position: relative; display: block;  max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\"\n  >\n    <span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n      style=\"padding-bottom: 81.81818181818181%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n    >\n      <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        style=\"width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;\"\n        alt=\"code\"\n        title=\"\"\n        src=\"/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/fb8a0/redux-thunk-6.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/1a291/redux-thunk-6.png 148w,\n/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/2bc4a/redux-thunk-6.png 295w,\n/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/fb8a0/redux-thunk-6.png 590w,\n/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/526de/redux-thunk-6.png 885w,\n/static/d0e33436d4127201240643600b22eca1/08cdb/redux-thunk-6.png 902w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n      />\n    </span>\n  </span>\n  \n  </a>\n    </p>\n<h2>A summary</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Create folders with the following name: types, actions, reducer, store, api.</li>\n<li>Inside types we add our constants.</li>\n<li>Import types inside our actions folders and export the action creators.</li>\n<li>If you’re doing an asynchronous request, then inside api add your requests.</li>\n<li>Configure your store.</li>\n<li>Connect it to Provider</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Conclusion</h2>\n<p>We learned about Redux principles in very few texts, but to truly grasp it we need to create a project, we’re actually gonna do two, one will be a small project where we will use all the concepts we learned today and for async we will use Redux Thunk. For the other project we will use Redux Saga, Selectors and Models, all of these concepts we will learn them in another post before doing said project.</p>\n<p>See you on the next post.</p>\n<p>Sincerely,</p>\n<p><strong>Eng Adrian Beria.</strong></p>","frontmatter":{"title":"Redux Thunk","date":"February 20, 2020"}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/10-redux-thunk/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/7-Redux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"Redux"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/9-setting-redux/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"How to setup Redux"}}}}